<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-inverse-variation-prep" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Inverse Variation and Negative Powers Prep Activities</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Two varying quantities <m>Q_1</m> and <m>Q_2</m> have an <term>inversely proportional relationship</term> when the product of the quantities is constant. That is, <m>Q_1</m> and <m>Q_2</m> have an inversely proportional relationship when 
      <me>
        c = Q_2 Q_1
      </me>
      always has the same value. We call <m>c</m> the <term>constant of proportionality</term>.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <investigation xml:id="pa-inverse-variation-workers-time">
    <introduction>
        <p>
            Angel and his friends run a painting business in the summer. Suppose it takes 2 of them 6 hours to paint a medium-sized room, and the amount of time needed and the number of painters are inversely proportional.
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                What is <m>c</m>, the constant of proportionality?
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Complete the table below, showing the relationship between painting time and number of painters.
            </p>
            <table>
                <title>Relationship Between Painting Time and Number of Painters</title>
                <tabular halign="center" top="minor" bottom = "minor" right="minor" left="minor">
                    <row header="yes">
                        <cell>Time, <m>T</m> (Hours)</cell>
                        <cell>Num Painters, <m>P</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell></cell>
                        <cell>1</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>6</cell>
                        <cell>2</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell></cell>
                        <cell>3</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell></cell>
                        <cell>4</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>2</cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Describe in words and with a formula how you found the missing information in the table.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Select the correct options to complete the sentence: <q>As the number of painters increases, the amount of time it takes to paint the room increases/decreases.</q>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
  </investigation>

